nd protect them selves. In my opinion the sooner all public schools are shut down and our educational system is privatized the sooner we as parents will have control over our childrens future. The proof is in the pudding, at a private school the employees answer to the parents. In the public schools the employees could care less about our opinions. I advise all parents to take the money available for private education through vouchers away from the public system and spend it wisely with the private school of your choice. public schools loose enough students and the only waythey will be able to meet their primary goal of self perpetuation will be by changing their mind set and improving the education of ourchildren so more parents will quit using private education. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1082" language="en" documentId="2509" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Mark 51" date="Aug 29, 2013 9:07PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="7" thumbsDown="0" origId="2509" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1082"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>